{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8c2da2e6-a43c-4f08-aeb9-aa51dd47ca59","content":"I can help you analyze the dump! Unfortunately, none of my specialized skills cover dump **analysis** (only collection and symbolication of specific crash log formats).\n\nHowever, I can help you interactively using CLI tools. Here's what I'd suggest:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** — the primary cross-platform tool for analyzing .NET crash dumps\n2. **`lldb` with SOS** — for deeper native + managed analysis on Linux\n\nLet me check what's available and locate your dump file:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01VUDQFrPdyhDpupCjVmzXxN","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Setting up dump analysis"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01BTNf5bpEUwkP2AHy8KVoNe","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"which dotnet-dump 2>/dev/null; which lldb 2>/dev/null; dotnet tool list -g 2>/dev/null | head -5; ls *.dmp 2>/dev/null; find /tmp/sv-b9c2a9b4669045fe9f23bc3fbaadcaac -name '*.dmp' -maxdepth 2 2>/dev/null","description":"Check available tools and dump files","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check available tools and dump files"}],"interactionId":"5b38b5c7-f605-4590-b8e7-a84961df66b8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at what tools and skills are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I don't see a specific skill for analyzing .dmp crash dump files. The skills available are:\n- analyzing-dotnet-performance - for performance anti-patterns in code\n- android-tombstone-symbolication - for Android tombstone files\n- apple-crash-symbolication - for Apple .ips crash logs\n- clr-activation-debugging - for CLR activation issues\n- dotnet-trace-collect - for collecting diagnostic artifacts\n\n\n- dump-collect - for configuring and collecting crash dumps (explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing